race.comment: MORAINE MILEY (7) doesn't win out of turn but recent form sound. Has hit the frame the last two runs, the latest when third (22.73) at this track. Has a good record here at this journey. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Capable of going well again. HENRY BALE (1) comes off an average run last start when fifth at this track over 390m behind Harajuku Lass (22.74) in a Grade 5. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and five minor placings to his credit. Cannot be taken lightly. PAW PASCAL (3) has a strong record this journey here with three wins and a minor from five starts. Was out of the placings last time (22.80) at Ballarat in a Grade 5, finishing fourth and beaten 3 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. NEENA BALE (8) looks an each-way chance.
